## DEEP MODE (45 minutes)

For multi-session chronicles, intensive personal-horror play, or first-time engagement with the genre's heavier elements. Add everything below.

### **HUMANITY-LOSS PERMISSIONS**

V:tM's central mechanic is the slow erosion of Humanity. This is the genre engine — but it is also where personal-horror content lives. Be explicit:

- ☐ I want my character to lose Humanity over the chronicle (the genre's intended arc)
- ☐ I want my character to MAYBE lose Humanity depending on choices
- ☐ I want my character to RESIST Humanity loss as the central drama
- ☐ I want to explore Wassail (full loss to the Beast) at chronicle end
- ☐ I want NEVER to fully Wassail; ending must preserve some humanity

**Specific Humanity-loss content I will / will not engage with:**

- Stains from feeding choices: ☐ Yes  ☐ Veil  ☐ No
- Stains from violation of personal Convictions: ☐ Yes  ☐ Veil  ☐ No
- Stains from harm to Touchstones: ☐ Yes  ☐ Veil  ☐ No
- Stains from unintended frenzy outcomes: ☐ Yes  ☐ Veil  ☐ No
- Loss of Touchstone (death, alienation, betrayal): ☐ Yes  ☐ Veil  ☐ No
